						               													<description>Hermit Boxes' is a two player game from Games magazine, March 2013. It can be played on a 4x4 or a 6x6 board. At the start of the game, the board is empty. Off the board is a supply of three dimensional rectangular pieces having dimensions of 1x1x2 units, where a unit is about the same length as the side of a square on the board. The pieces come in three colors - red, yellow and blue.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player in turn chooses a piece of any color and places it on the board either upright, so that it covers just one square, or on its side, so that it covers two squares.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pieces may only be placed on empty squares, and a piece may not be placed next to a piece of the same color, not even diagonally.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player who is unable to make a legal placement loses the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
